  "text": "where s i j = ∑ k, 0<d ik <d i j w k is the total amount of communication originating from locations at a distance shorter than d i j from location i and C i is a normalization factor ensuring that the predicted total activity of each node is the same as the actual one, i.e. ∑ j =i T Rad i j = ∑ j =i T i j . The model is otherwise parameter-free. We also applied the generalized version of the radiation model proposed in [CITATION_1] , introducing a parameter λ which can be interpreted in our case as a fraction of individuals people will not consider as potential contacts because of lack of information about them of other reasons. This version of the radiation model can be written as",
